parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
multiple warning lights illuminate
including "Service Engine Immediately" and "Engine Overheating" (even if the engine is not overheating)
the vehicle is unable to start
and the ECU is diagnosed as faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including issues with the power locks, horn, airbag system, and brake system, which can lead to accidents or compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The power locks malfunction
the horn is unresponsive
the airbag system warning indicator illuminates
the brake system warning indicator illuminates
and the vehicle's electrical system exhibits unusual behavior
such as cycling through multiple warning messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to experience difficulty starting, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has difficulty starting
the alternator needs to be replaced
and the replacement part is on backorder
indicating a widespread issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Hatch and Emergency Release Mechanism Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch and emergency release mechanism can cause difficulty accessing the vehicle in emergency situations, which can compromise safety.
symptoms: The rear hatch does not open
the emergency release mechanism is difficult to access
and the handle tailgate lock release mechanism is susceptible to water damage and corrosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
"Airbag system service required" message on the dashboard
no airbag deployment in the event of a crash
failure to diagnose or repair the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Improperly Installed Driver Seat Mounted Airbag Wiring
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper installation of the driver seat mounted airbag wiring can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
"Airbag system service required" message on the dashboard
recall notice for improperly installed airbag wiring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
"Airbag system service required" message on the dashboard
airbag light will not turn off
failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Overheating and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission overheating issue can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to a sudden loss of speed, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The "Transmission Overheating" message is displayed on the instrument panel
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle slows down independently
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the transmission slips
and the engine RPMs jump wildly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the engine RPMs jump wildly
the vehicle loses power
and error codes such as P1778 appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Fluid Leak and Defective Mold
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission fluid leak can cause the transmission to fail, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
oil drips from underneath the motor and transmission
and the transmission mold is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially in rainy or snowy conditions, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working
the wipers fail to clear the windshield
the wipers stick in an upright position
the wipers work intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks for drivers and passengers, as well as frustration and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Parts are unavailable for recall repairs
dealerships are unable to perform recall repairs
manufacturers are unresponsive or unhelpful
vehicle owners are left without a safe or functional vehicle.
